1
00:01:43,930 --> 00:01:47,050
The Straw Hat crew's
planned rendezvous at Cacao Island

2
00:01:47,050 --> 00:01:49,200
is in 32 minutes.

3
00:01:50,950 --> 00:01:52,550
Nobody has come out yet.

4
00:01:52,550 --> 00:01:55,250
I guess the battle is dragging on.

5
00:01:55,250 --> 00:01:58,360
Is there any chance that
Big Brother Katakuri might lose?

6
00:01:58,360 --> 00:02:01,810
What?! You think there's
a chance Katakuri might lose?!

7
00:02:01,810 --> 00:02:04,010
Newji! Are you...

8
00:02:04,010 --> 00:02:05,980
serious?!

9
00:02:06,610 --> 00:02:09,150
The chance of that is zero!

10
00:02:09,150 --> 00:02:10,310
Ouch!

11
00:02:10,310 --> 00:02:16,220
Why did you hit me?! I'm Newsan!
I wasn't the one who said that!

12
00:02:16,220 --> 00:02:20,000
Katakuri will never be defeated
for the rest of his life!

13
00:02:20,420 --> 00:02:22,830
He's right, you idiot!

14
00:02:22,830 --> 00:02:26,630
Big Brother Katakuri is a perfect man!

15
00:02:26,630 --> 00:02:30,050
Ouch! I'm Newshi!

16
00:02:30,050 --> 00:02:32,720
I'm sorry, Newsan, Newshi...

17
00:02:33,740 --> 00:02:35,170
Ouch!

18
00:02:35,170 --> 00:02:36,540
That's what you get!

19
00:02:36,540 --> 00:02:37,950
What?!

20
00:02:37,950 --> 00:02:39,540
You idiot! You idiot!

21
00:02:39,540 --> 00:02:43,730
But... he hasn't contacted us in a while...
It's strange.

22
00:02:43,730 --> 00:02:46,750
If I were Straw Hat, here's what I would do:

23
00:02:46,750 --> 00:02:50,400
he is planning to rendezvous with his crew
at one a.m., here on Cacao Island.

24
00:02:50,950 --> 00:02:56,370
In other words,
his crew won't arrive until one a.m...

25
00:02:56,370 --> 00:03:01,710
If I were in his shoes, I'd capture Sister Brûlée,
the only key to the Mirro-world,

26
00:03:01,710 --> 00:03:06,550
and wait out the clock
in the Mirro-world or on other islands!

27
00:03:06,550 --> 00:03:11,300
That makes sense!
Sister Brûlée is currently missing, after all!

28
00:03:11,300 --> 00:03:12,430
That's right!

29
00:03:12,430 --> 00:03:17,390
In other words, it's highly likely that Straw Hat Luffy
will try and run away from his duel with Katakuri...

30
00:03:17,390 --> 00:03:21,870
and come out of this mirror at one a.m. sharp...

31
00:03:21,870 --> 00:03:23,480
I see... I agree.

32
00:03:23,480 --> 00:03:27,400
Sister Brûlée is a bit dense,
so she's easy to capture.

33
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:31,880
Akimeg, our sister might be listening
through the mirror.

34
00:03:31,880 --> 00:03:33,450
Oh, oops!

35
00:03:33,450 --> 00:03:37,170
We've got 30 minutes...
We need to stay alert.

36
00:03:37,170 --> 00:03:39,750
Hurry up and come out, Straw Hat!

37
00:03:39,750 --> 00:03:43,500
I'll chop you in half with my sickle!

38
00:04:00,640 --> 00:04:03,600
Are they all fighters?

39
00:04:03,600 --> 00:04:07,980
Seems like that's the only mirror
that they left intact...

40
00:04:11,190 --> 00:04:14,650
When Luffy comes out,
we need to leave immediately...

41
00:04:14,650 --> 00:04:17,320
or both of us will be killed...

42
00:04:19,620 --> 00:04:24,080
When Luffy comes out,
that'll be when we part ways...

43
00:04:24,080 --> 00:04:25,210
Pudding-cha...

44
00:04:25,960 --> 00:04:27,830
So far away!

45
00:04:27,830 --> 00:04:30,360
Can you hear me, Pudding-chan ?

46
00:04:30,360 --> 00:04:33,610
D-D-D... Don't look at me!

47
00:04:33,610 --> 00:04:35,970
I-I-I am listening to you!

48
00:04:35,970 --> 00:04:37,200
Sanji...

49
00:04:37,200 --> 00:04:38,470
...-san !

50
00:04:41,890 --> 00:04:45,180
Looking back, we sure met
during unusual circumstances...

51
00:04:51,270 --> 00:04:56,530
This is your bride-to-be...
Madam Charlotte Pudding!

52
00:04:56,860 --> 00:04:59,960
Let's get married tomorrow.

53
00:05:03,970 --> 00:05:07,350
I had a lot of fun with you, Pudding-chan,

54
00:05:07,350 --> 00:05:10,270
but it's almost time for us to say goodbye.

55
00:05:10,270 --> 00:05:11,730
Thank you for everything!

56
00:05:19,570 --> 00:05:24,630
I fooled you and tried to kill you...

57
00:05:24,630 --> 00:05:27,370
So don't thank me, Sanji-san !

58
00:05:27,370 --> 00:05:30,660
I want to apologize!

59
00:05:30,660 --> 00:05:34,040
I really need to apologize!

60
00:05:52,270 --> 00:05:54,000
Shut up!

61
00:05:57,480 --> 00:06:01,610
No! No! I did it again!

62
00:06:01,610 --> 00:06:05,110
You're right!
We're enemies, after all!

63
00:06:05,650 --> 00:06:09,430
To you, Pudding-chan,
our marriage was just a trap.

64
00:06:09,430 --> 00:06:14,620
The whole thing was staged
by the Big Mom Pirates...

65
00:06:17,420 --> 00:06:18,420
But...

66
00:06:19,250 --> 00:06:21,710
maybe it was unpleasant
for you, Pudding-chan...

67
00:06:24,540 --> 00:06:28,640
but I'm glad that you were the one
in the role of my fiancée, Pudding-chan !

68
00:06:41,070 --> 00:06:43,070
Ah, no...

69
00:06:43,430 --> 00:06:46,720
I'm sorry! I didn't mean to insult you!

70
00:06:46,720 --> 00:06:49,130
No! Stop crying!

71
00:06:49,130 --> 00:06:50,660
Stop, tears!

72
00:06:50,660 --> 00:06:52,470
I-I'm sorry!

73
00:06:52,470 --> 00:06:54,920
I didn't mean that, Pudding-chan !

74
00:06:56,290 --> 00:06:58,440
H-Hey, Sanji...

75
00:06:58,440 --> 00:06:59,880
...-san...

76
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:03,880
Could you do me a favor?!

77
00:07:05,340 --> 00:07:09,220
Just one last thing...

78
00:07:11,220 --> 00:07:13,620
This is all I ask of you!

79
00:08:42,690 --> 00:08:46,110
I can't believe they've survived this long!

80
00:08:46,110 --> 00:08:48,160
The Straw Hat crew...

81
00:08:48,160 --> 00:08:52,220
If they're able to escape
from such an all-out attack formation,

82
00:08:52,220 --> 00:08:54,700
it'll be unbelievably big news!

83
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:58,590
Shut up, Morgans!
You won't be getting a scoop!

84
00:08:58,590 --> 00:09:01,310
In order to ensure we avoid that,

85
00:09:01,310 --> 00:09:05,400
we swallowed our pride
and sent a horde of soldiers to Cacao Island!

86
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:10,710
Even if Gold Roger, the former pirate king,
were to come out of the mirror,

87
00:09:10,710 --> 00:09:13,300
he wouldn't be able to escape!

88
00:09:13,300 --> 00:09:17,370
Once we catch them all, we'll execute them
and line up their heads for display;

89
00:09:17,370 --> 00:09:20,350
you should put that
on the front page tomorrow.

90
00:09:20,850 --> 00:09:22,490
It'll serve as a warning!

91
00:09:24,230 --> 00:09:27,770
How vulgar...
There's no need to go that far.

92
00:09:28,860 --> 00:09:31,630
Don't be silly!
It's almost too kind!

93
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:34,800
We'll get good news soon!

94
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:40,040
There's no way that one ship can
get through our gigantic fleet!

95
00:09:46,460 --> 00:09:48,550
Wait!

96
00:09:50,050 --> 00:09:52,720
Give me the cake!

97
00:09:54,340 --> 00:09:56,180
The sails are on fire!

98
00:09:56,180 --> 00:09:58,350
Put it out now! We're gonna sink!

99
00:10:00,310 --> 00:10:03,760
We can't go on-rero, Father!
This is the end-rero !

100
00:10:03,760 --> 00:10:06,780
We're gonna die before we
reach the island-rero !

101
00:10:06,780 --> 00:10:09,480
Let's throw the cake off and flee, Father!

102
00:10:10,020 --> 00:10:12,110
Don't falter now!

103
00:10:12,110 --> 00:10:13,360
Rero ?

104
00:10:14,560 --> 00:10:18,830
We may have all come
from different places,

105
00:10:18,830 --> 00:10:20,830
but in the face of death,

106
00:10:20,830 --> 00:10:23,580
we should stick together!

107
00:10:23,600 --> 00:10:26,420
Father!

108
00:10:27,710 --> 00:10:28,960
I see it!

109
00:10:32,760 --> 00:10:34,260
It's Puffs Island!

110
00:10:34,260 --> 00:10:36,140
Rero !

111
00:10:36,140 --> 00:10:40,100
We're almost there!
Stay strong, guys!

112
00:10:40,100 --> 00:10:44,520
Yeah!

113
00:10:50,580 --> 00:10:53,760
We'll make it by one a.m.,
just as we promised!

114
00:10:55,050 --> 00:10:59,270
But what I'm worried about is the key
to escaping the Mirro-world: Brûlée.

115
00:10:59,270 --> 00:11:04,150
Even if Luffy wins,
he can't get out of there without Brûlée!

116
00:11:04,150 --> 00:11:08,900
I don't think Luffy is the type of person
who can think that far ahead...

117
00:11:08,900 --> 00:11:10,940
You're right! He can't!

118
00:11:10,940 --> 00:11:13,360
He definitely can't!
What should we do?!

119
00:11:13,360 --> 00:11:16,640
First of all, we don't even know
if he knows the current time...

120
00:11:16,640 --> 00:11:18,100
That too?!

121
00:11:18,610 --> 00:11:20,720
So much could go wrong...

122
00:11:21,830 --> 00:11:23,950
but we believe in you, Luffy!

123
00:11:54,470 --> 00:11:57,570
Even when he falls, he falls forward...

124
00:12:12,650 --> 00:12:14,690
Listen carefully, Luffy!

125
00:12:15,190 --> 00:12:17,900
At the earliest, we'll arrive in 10 hours!

126
00:12:17,900 --> 00:12:19,490
That's around one a.m.!

127
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:22,890
So after you beat that guy up,

128
00:12:22,890 --> 00:12:25,930
search for a mirror that leads to Cacao Island!

129
00:12:25,930 --> 00:12:27,980
We'll meet you there!

130
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:34,330
What time is it right now?

131
00:13:01,990 --> 00:13:04,160
Someday... will you...

132
00:13:06,740 --> 00:13:09,410
come back here to defeat Big Mom?

133
00:13:13,830 --> 00:13:15,920
Of course! I am the man

134
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:18,680
who will be king of the pirates!

135
00:13:31,640 --> 00:13:34,430
You're seeing pretty far into the future...

136
00:14:34,120 --> 00:14:37,140
Branch, let's go...

137
00:14:37,420 --> 00:14:39,290
What? Branch?

138
00:14:39,960 --> 00:14:42,170
She escaped!

139
00:14:42,170 --> 00:14:45,550
Oh, no! I can't
get out of here without her...

140
00:14:45,550 --> 00:14:47,220
W-What should I do?

141
00:14:49,310 --> 00:14:51,010
I don't have time...

142
00:14:51,010 --> 00:14:53,770
Big Brother!

143
00:14:54,730 --> 00:14:58,730
Big Brother Katakuri!

144
00:14:59,860 --> 00:15:01,030
Branch!

145
00:15:01,030 --> 00:15:03,710
The name's Brûlée, Straw Hat!

146
00:15:03,710 --> 00:15:07,240
What foul tricks did you use
to take down my big brother?!

147
00:15:07,240 --> 00:15:09,860
So you were able to defeat Katakuri!

148
00:15:09,860 --> 00:15:11,990
I can't believe it!

149
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:13,330
You're...

150
00:15:16,500 --> 00:15:19,300
I am... Nazoms!

151
00:15:16,500 --> 00:15:18,730
Nazo: Mysterious

152
00:15:20,920 --> 00:15:25,640
In order to help you escape from here,
I captured Brûlée and have been waiting for you!

153
00:15:25,640 --> 00:15:27,410
So you're okay...

154
00:15:28,180 --> 00:15:29,610
Pekoms!

155
00:15:32,310 --> 00:15:36,830
Yeah! Big Bro Pedro sacrificed himself
to save your lives!

156
00:15:36,830 --> 00:15:40,680
So I can't let you die here!

157
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:45,950
Come on, Straw Hat!
Let's go meet your friends at Cacao Island!

158
00:15:45,950 --> 00:15:46,920
Okay!

159
00:15:46,920 --> 00:15:48,880
Let go of me!

160
00:15:51,030 --> 00:15:54,080
There it is! Cacao Island!

161
00:15:58,170 --> 00:15:59,710
How many are there?!

162
00:16:01,170 --> 00:16:03,410
That's a massive fleet!

163
00:16:04,090 --> 00:16:06,720
Sanji-kun ! How is it over there?

164
00:16:07,590 --> 00:16:09,520
Luffy hasn't come out yet.

165
00:16:09,520 --> 00:16:11,710
Don't get close
to the fleet at the shore.

166
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:16,930
I'll find a way to get Luffy to the ship!

167
00:16:22,270 --> 00:16:25,730
Does everyone have their weapons ready?!

168
00:16:25,730 --> 00:16:29,370
Yeah!

169
00:16:29,370 --> 00:16:32,570
If he's gonna come out,
it'll be in five minutes!

170
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:37,360
Now, come on out...

171
00:16:37,360 --> 00:16:40,370
Straw Hat Luffy!

172
00:16:43,250 --> 00:16:44,950
Four minutes to go...

173
00:16:53,430 --> 00:16:54,500
That's...

174
00:17:00,890 --> 00:17:02,520
I'm sure it is!

175
00:17:08,380 --> 00:17:11,240
The Straw Hat crew's ship!

176
00:17:14,820 --> 00:17:16,930
It looks like they saw us!

177
00:17:16,930 --> 00:17:19,810
How could they assemble that many ships?

178
00:17:19,810 --> 00:17:23,970
Sink Straw Hat's ship!

179
00:17:25,720 --> 00:17:27,140
Here they come!

180
00:17:27,140 --> 00:17:30,410
Oh no! We're gonna die!

181
00:17:30,410 --> 00:17:33,250
Luffy, hurry up!

182
00:17:33,250 --> 00:17:35,060
Keep our distance from the island!

183
00:17:35,080 --> 00:17:36,690
All right!

184
00:17:41,690 --> 00:17:44,780
What should we do, Smoothie?!

185
00:17:44,780 --> 00:17:50,490
We'll continue to reinforce the back side!
They have nowhere to run.

186
00:17:50,490 --> 00:17:55,910
The Totto Land Grand Fleet
led by Snack is ahead of them,

187
00:17:55,910 --> 00:17:58,500
and our fleet is behind them.

188
00:17:59,340 --> 00:18:02,800
Even if they somehow
make it to Cacao Island,

189
00:18:02,800 --> 00:18:06,330
Brother Oven's army is waiting for them.

190
00:18:07,470 --> 00:18:10,230
They're already cornered rats.

191
00:18:11,310 --> 00:18:13,850
This is their final destination!

192
00:18:16,010 --> 00:18:18,980
Link the transponder snails!

193
00:18:18,980 --> 00:18:22,940
We need information from all angles.

194
00:18:22,940 --> 00:18:25,230
Certainly, Seigneur Mont d'Or.

195
00:18:27,950 --> 00:18:30,330
Prepare yourself, you brat!

196
00:18:30,330 --> 00:18:34,620
Come on out, Straw Hat!

197
00:18:42,790 --> 00:18:44,090
Come on!

198
00:18:44,090 --> 00:18:46,300
Hurry up, Luffy!

199
00:18:51,760 --> 00:18:56,980
Help!

200
00:18:56,980 --> 00:18:59,020
Sulong?

201
00:18:59,020 --> 00:19:00,560
That's right!

202
00:19:00,560 --> 00:19:06,110
We Minks can transform into our primal form
by looking at the full moon!

203
00:19:06,110 --> 00:19:10,640
But I've always had trouble controlling it.

204
00:19:10,640 --> 00:19:15,160
When I turn Sulong,
I'm nothing but a rampaging monster.

205
00:19:15,160 --> 00:19:16,540
A monster?

206
00:19:16,540 --> 00:19:20,880
I'll run wild and destroy
everything around me!

207
00:19:20,880 --> 00:19:24,500
No one's voice can reach me, except...

208
00:19:25,960 --> 00:19:28,630
for one person!

209
00:19:28,630 --> 00:19:30,930
That person was Big Bro Pedro!

210
00:19:47,030 --> 00:19:49,150
Stop, Pekoms!

211
00:19:49,150 --> 00:19:56,510
For some reason, Big Bro's voice was the only one
that could calm me down in that mindless state!

212
00:20:01,580 --> 00:20:02,450
Pedro...

213
00:20:04,410 --> 00:20:10,170
So there's no one left in this world
who can stop my rampage!

214
00:20:12,500 --> 00:20:16,090
Listen, Straw Hat.
It's the full moon tonight!

215
00:20:20,090 --> 00:20:23,720
When I go out to Cacao Island
through the mirror,

216
00:20:23,720 --> 00:20:26,930
I'll transform into my Sulong form!

217
00:20:27,560 --> 00:20:33,650
When I go out of control,
that'll be your chance to escape from Cacao Island!

218
00:20:33,650 --> 00:20:36,440
You idiot! It's no use, Pekoms!

219
00:20:36,650 --> 00:20:38,450
You damn traitor!

220
00:20:38,450 --> 00:20:42,220
There is a force at Cacao Island
large enough to launch a war!

221
00:20:42,220 --> 00:20:46,660
Even if you transform,
they'll take you down instantly and it'll be over!

222
00:20:49,120 --> 00:20:50,210
I'm gonna fall!

223
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:53,300
Shut up, Brûlée!

224
00:20:53,670 --> 00:20:55,920
We're almost there, Straw Hat!

225
00:20:56,630 --> 00:20:59,470
Big Bro Pedro sacrificed himself!

226
00:20:59,470 --> 00:21:02,930
No matter what,
don't let it go to waste!

227
00:21:06,890 --> 00:21:07,980
Okay!

228
00:21:09,440 --> 00:21:11,200
Thanks!

229
00:21:11,200 --> 00:21:14,240
Now, do your job for us!

230
00:21:14,240 --> 00:21:15,110
What?

231
00:21:15,110 --> 00:21:19,610
Let's go!

232
00:21:25,560 --> 00:21:27,980
It's coming from inside the mirror!

233
00:21:27,980 --> 00:21:31,730
Help!

234
00:21:32,210 --> 00:21:34,380
Isn't that Sister Brûlée?!

235
00:21:34,380 --> 00:21:37,630
Just as we thought,
she was captured by Straw Hat.

236
00:21:37,630 --> 00:21:39,300
That bastard!

237
00:21:46,220 --> 00:21:48,880
He's coming! Take aim and fire!

238
00:22:04,410 --> 00:22:05,620
What?!

239
00:22:05,620 --> 00:22:07,360
Is that...?!

240
00:22:07,360 --> 00:22:09,700
Pekoms!

241
00:22:09,700 --> 00:22:11,000
What?!

242
00:22:12,960 --> 00:22:14,120
I'm Nazoms!

243
00:22:14,120 --> 00:22:16,750
Pekoms! Why are you here?!

244
00:22:16,750 --> 00:22:17,360
What?

245
00:22:20,710 --> 00:22:24,610
D-Don't move, Big Mom Pirates!

246
00:22:24,610 --> 00:22:27,030
I-If you do something stupid...

247
00:22:27,030 --> 00:22:33,520
I'll blow your precious sister
Brûlée's brains out!

248
00:22:33,520 --> 00:22:35,310
Brûlée!

249
00:22:34,370 --> 00:22:35,320
Sister Brûlée!

250
00:22:35,320 --> 00:22:37,560
Stop it, Pekoms!

251
00:22:37,560 --> 00:22:39,940
Pekoms, what are you thinking?!

252
00:22:39,940 --> 00:22:41,940
Why don't you calm down?!

253
00:22:41,940 --> 00:22:43,900
Let go of Sister Brûlée!

254
00:22:43,900 --> 00:22:49,480
Help! Everyone!

255
00:22:49,490 --> 00:22:53,660
My identity was going to be revealed
by going Sulong anyway...

256
00:22:56,790 --> 00:22:58,500
so it doesn't matter now!

257
00:23:08,040 --> 00:23:11,930
I'll keep Straw Hat alive!

258
00:23:11,940 --> 00:23:16,340
He's the man that
Big Bro Pedro bet his life on!

259
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:29,460
No way!

260
00:23:31,620 --> 00:23:33,830
He's trying to turn Sulong!

261
00:23:33,830 --> 00:23:35,610
Stop, Pekoms!

262
00:23:35,610 --> 00:23:37,710
You won't be able to control yourself!

263
00:23:39,210 --> 00:23:41,950
No!

264
00:23:43,130 --> 00:23:44,590
Hold him down!

265
00:23:44,590 --> 00:23:46,720
It's too late...

266
00:23:46,720 --> 00:23:48,890
Prepare yourselves!

267
00:23:49,850 --> 00:23:51,600
Hey!

268
00:23:51,600 --> 00:23:52,940
You bastard!

269
00:23:53,760 --> 00:23:57,040
Hey, hey, what's going on here?

270
00:23:57,040 --> 00:24:02,270
Neither Katakuri nor Straw Hat
came out of the mirror!

271
00:24:02,270 --> 00:24:05,360
How dare you point a gun at my sister...

272
00:24:05,360 --> 00:24:07,700
for no reason?!

273
00:24:12,160 --> 00:24:12,680
Ouch!

274
00:24:12,680 --> 00:24:14,580
Big Brother!

275
00:24:16,580 --> 00:24:17,750
Heat...

276
00:24:20,250 --> 00:24:21,880
Cross!

277
00:24:21,880 --> 00:24:24,170
Ouch!

278
00:24:24,170 --> 00:24:25,970
No!

279
00:24:25,970 --> 00:24:27,590
Yes!

280
00:24:34,510 --> 00:24:35,850
That's Straw Hat!

281
00:24:42,270 --> 00:24:43,420
Luffy!

282
00:24:53,030 --> 00:24:54,080
This is Sanji!

283
00:24:54,080 --> 00:24:55,210
It's Sanji!

284
00:24:55,210 --> 00:24:56,230
Luffy...

285
00:24:57,120 --> 00:24:58,300
made it!

286
00:24:59,750 --> 00:25:01,880
Yes!

287
00:25:06,720 --> 00:25:08,010
It's Straw Hat!

288
00:25:08,010 --> 00:25:10,050
Pekoms was hiding him!

289
00:25:10,050 --> 00:25:12,050
Get him!

290
00:25:12,050 --> 00:25:15,700
He somehow was able
to outwit Big Brother Katakuri and escape.

291
00:25:15,700 --> 00:25:17,680
That's pretty impressive!

292
00:25:17,680 --> 00:25:20,420
I'm gonna go first!

293
00:25:20,420 --> 00:25:21,980
Yahoo!

294
00:25:23,970 --> 00:25:24,940
Look up!

295
00:25:27,280 --> 00:25:29,740
You should know...

296
00:25:29,740 --> 00:25:32,490
that jumping makes you an easy target!

297
00:25:34,830 --> 00:25:37,450
Just surrender!

298
00:25:42,300 --> 00:25:43,920
Brother Raisin!

299
00:25:44,500 --> 00:25:46,290
Who is that guy?!

300
00:25:47,000 --> 00:25:48,090
Sanji!

301
00:25:48,920 --> 00:25:50,170
Did you win?!

302
00:25:50,170 --> 00:25:51,400
Yeah!

303
00:25:54,970 --> 00:25:56,270
As expected!

304
00:25:57,180 --> 00:25:58,890
They're trying to escape through the sky!

305
00:25:58,890 --> 00:26:01,060
That's Black Leg!

306
00:26:01,060 --> 00:26:02,200
How naive...

307
00:26:02,200 --> 00:26:04,100
We were prepared for this!

308
00:26:04,100 --> 00:26:07,320
We can use Moon Walk, too!

309
00:26:07,320 --> 00:26:08,530
One!

310
00:26:08,530 --> 00:26:09,610
Two!

311
00:26:09,610 --> 00:26:10,780
Three!

312
00:26:10,780 --> 00:26:11,950
Four!

313
00:26:11,950 --> 00:26:13,240
Five!

314
00:26:19,240 --> 00:26:22,560
Make it so he'll
never see the full moon again!

315
00:26:50,120 --> 00:26:53,420
Pekoms!

316
00:26:53,420 --> 00:26:55,000
Not paying attention....

317
00:26:55,800 --> 00:26:59,660
is disrespectful!

318
00:27:05,420 --> 00:27:10,390
When you're vastly outnumbered,
it's meaningless,

319
00:27:10,390 --> 00:27:13,260
no matter how hard you struggle.

320
00:27:15,770 --> 00:27:16,910
Dammit!

321
00:27:20,130 --> 00:27:20,740
What?!

322
00:27:21,870 --> 00:27:24,500
There was an explosion at the harbor!

323
00:27:26,340 --> 00:27:28,800
What is that?!

324
00:27:28,800 --> 00:27:31,470
Hey, what happened?!

325
00:27:31,480 --> 00:27:35,010
The ships by the coast are burning!

326
00:27:35,010 --> 00:27:36,560
What's going on?!

327
00:27:36,560 --> 00:27:37,740
Was there a bomb?!

328
00:27:37,740 --> 00:27:40,470
It's a fleet, Snack-sama !

329
00:27:40,470 --> 00:27:42,010
Who the hell is it?!

330
00:27:42,010 --> 00:27:43,190
I-It's...

331
00:27:43,190 --> 00:27:45,240
Germa's fleet!

332
00:27:46,410 --> 00:27:48,440
Why are they here?!

333
00:27:48,440 --> 00:27:51,520
They were supposed to have been
wiped out hours ago!

334
00:27:51,520 --> 00:27:54,500
Next, prepare to fire!

335
00:27:54,500 --> 00:27:56,720
Germa 66!

336
00:27:56,720 --> 00:27:59,660
Why are they here?!

337
00:28:06,280 --> 00:28:08,010
Dammit!

338
00:28:20,360 --> 00:28:22,440
You bastards!

339
00:28:22,440 --> 00:28:26,290
Thanks for taking care of us
at the tea party,

340
00:28:26,290 --> 00:28:27,990
Big Mom Pirates!

341
00:28:27,990 --> 00:28:30,790
Germa 66!

342
00:28:31,490 --> 00:28:33,660
Why are you guys here?!

343
00:28:33,660 --> 00:28:36,250
What a coincidence, Sanji.

344
00:28:42,980 --> 00:28:46,190
We also wanted a chance...

345
00:28:46,190 --> 00:28:49,170
to shake things up!

